-- Taiwan President Ma Congratulates China's Liu Xiaobo on Nobel Peace Prize
-- B y   T i m   C u l p a n
-- 2010-10-08T13:04:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/taiwan-president-ma-congratulates-china-s-liu-xiaobo-on-nobel-peace-prize.html
Taiwan President  Ma Ying-jeou 
congratulated China’s  Liu Xiaobo  on winning the Nobel Peace
Prize.         "Mainland China’s economic development has impressed the
world, if it can make progress and breakthroughs in human
rights this would be in line with the goal of a peaceful rise,
and win recognition from Taiwanese people and the international
community," Ma said in a statement posted on the presidential
website today.  "Not only is it a great personal honor for Liu Xiaobo, in
terms of mainland China’s human rights development, it’s of
historic importance to the global Chinese community," the
statement said.            Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
